message.content:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he could type 9 words per minute. So, in 5 minutes, he would have typed:
9 words/minute * 5 minutes = 45 words.

After he broke his arm, he could only type 6 words per minute with his left hand. In 5 minutes, he would have typed:
6 words/minute * 5 minutes = 30 words.

The difference in the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is:
45 words (before) - 30 words (after) = 15 words.
